               <head>Copy of court roll; Glemsford; 1515</head>
               <msContents>
                  <textLang mainLang="la">Latin</textLang>
                  <msItem>
                     <p> <supplied><placeName key="place_104322">Glemsford</placeName>.</supplied> At a court of <persName>
                           <forename>William</forename> 
                           <surname>Medewold</surname>, esq.</persName>, 
                  held the <origDate when="1515-10-09">Tuesday on the feast of St. Dionisius, 7 Hen. VIII (9 Oct. 1515)</origDate>,
                  <persName>
                           <forename>John</forename> 
                           <surname>Hall</surname>
                        </persName> delivered into the hands of the
                  lord a little "pightell" of pasture for the use of <persName>
                           <forename>Walter</forename>
                           <surname>Berdfeld</surname></persName>, to hold the same according to the
                  custom of the manor. 
                  </p>
